 of people says that the gills are bitter.

00:00:38.939 --> 00:00:42.309
I don't really have a problem with them, so I you 
 don't have a problem with them leave them in.

00:00:42.309 --> 00:00:47.740
I am going to take mine out just so nobody will 
 complain about anything. It is the life I live.

00:00:47.740 --> 00:00:55.088
Next we are going to add olive oil, liquid 
 smoke, salt, and pepper to our mushroom caps.

00:00:55.088 --> 00:01:00.000
Place them in the oven and let them sit 
 under the broiler for about 3 minutes.

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:02.067
Next we are going to add our topping.

00:01:02.067 --> 00:01:07.593
I am going to use this tomato basil pasta 
 sauce by Newman's Own. It smells so good.

00:01:07.593 --> 00:01:14.234
I love basil. Then after your tomato sauce, we are 
 going to put on our cheese sauce, then pepperoni.

00:01:14.234 --> 00:01:19.273
I'm using these Yves veggie pepperoni, but you can use whatever 
 type of pepperoni you want . . . or not.

00:01:19.273 --> 00:01:24.265
And then a little bit of nutritional yeast, but these are 
 very versatile. You can use whatever toppings you want.

00:01:24.265 --> 00:01:32.717
They will probably all taste great together. Put those back under the 
 broiler for 5-7 minutes until they are golden brown 

00:01:32.717 --> 00:01:34.761
over the top. Nice hot and toasty, and backed through.

00:01:34.761 --> 00:01:36.711
That is it. It is so simple.

